org.mindswap.owl
Interface OWLReader

All Known Implementing Classes:
OWLReaderImpl
public interface OWLReader

OWL reader realize parsing and loading serialized OWL ontologies into (in-memory) KBs.

If Jena is used as the backing RDF library then repeated reads of the same ontology (including imported ontologies) may bypass the read and use cached in memory instances. This has an effect then in situations when read of some (imported) ontology initially failed (for some I/O related or syntactical reason): Only the first attempt will end by throwing an IOException then. Subsequent attempts to read the same ontology (even if it is an imported one) will end without an exception and its model will be empty. However, it is possible to (partially) clear the cache by invoking OWLKnowledgeBaseManager.clear(URI) on the KB manager associated to the KB. After doing so, the next attempt to read the same ontology will try to read the resource from its original location, thus, throwing an exception in case of failures.

Method Detail

read

OWLOntology read(java.net.URI url)
                 throws java.io.IOException
Reads a ontology from the given URL (file: and http:) and loads it into the KB to which this reader is associated. If the ontology imports other ontologies they will be read into the KB as well, provided that they can be located and accessed given their import URI.

Parameters:
url - The URL of the document to read (provided as a URI).
Returns:
The Ontology model.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - In case reading of the referenced ontology failed or was interrupted for some I/O related reason. If isIgnoreFailedImport() returns false, this exception may also be thrown if reading of some imported ontology (transitively) failed. However, there is an Jena specific detail caused by the its internal caching mechanism, see class JavaDoc.

setIgnoreFailedImport

void setIgnoreFailedImport(boolean ignore)
Set the way this reader handles the event if some imported ontology can not be found when reading the ontology that specifies the import. (Ontologies to import are specified in OWL using the owl:imports property).

Parameters:
ignore - If true the reader will ignore the event when some imported ontology could not be found (for whatever reason). The corresponding read method will then not throw an IOException for failed attempts to read an imported ontology.

isIgnoreFailedImport

boolean isIgnoreFailedImport()
The way this reader handles the event if some imported ontology can not be found when reading the ontology that specifies the import. (Ontologies to import are specified in OWL using the owl:imports property).

The default value of implementations should be false.

Returns:
If true the reader will ignore the event when some imported ontology could not be found (for whatever reason). The corresponding read method will then not throw an IOException for failed attempts to read an imported ontology.

setSyntax

void setSyntax(OWLSyntax syntax)
Set the format of documents to be subsequently read. Each implementation must use OWLSyntax.RDFXML by default, i.e., a reader assumes documents to have this format unless set to another supported format. Furthermore, implementations must support switching formats between consecutive reads, i.e., it is not a set once only property.

Parameters:
syntax - The format of ontology documents to be subsequently read.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the format is not supported.

supports

boolean supports(OWLSyntax syntax)
Check if documents of the given format can be read.

Parameters:
syntax - The source format.
Returns:
true if the given format is supported by this reader, false otherwise.
